Below is a drop‑in way to add the “Approach” box directly **below the hero** on `secondary-school-maths.html`, with typography, spacing, colors, and width all matched to your E/A Maths sections. I’m keeping the change **page‑scoped** (CSS goes in `assets/css/secondary-maths.css`) so the rest of the site is untouched. fileciteturn0file1 fileciteturn0file2 fileciteturn0file0

---

## 1) HTML — insert right after the hero

In `secondary-school-maths.html`, add this immediately after the closing `</section>` of the hero and **before** the Elementary Maths section:

```html
<!-- ===== Approach (new) ===== -->
<section class="section section--approach" id="approach" aria-labelledby="approach-title">
  <div class="approach-wrap">
    <article class="approach-box" role="region" aria-labelledby="approach-title">
      <h2 class="box-title" id="approach-title">My Approach to E Maths and A Maths</h2>

      <!-- Use paragraphs and list items as needed; sizes mirror E/A sections -->
      <div class="box-body split-text">
        <p>Start with foundations, then build confidence through structured drills and timely feedback.</p>
        <ul class="list--lg">
          <li>Short, concept‑first explanations before practice.</li>
          <li>Systematic drill sets that cover common exam patterns.</li>
          <li>Focused revision checklists and formula audits.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Approach is adjusted per student, with clear milestones and measurable progress each term.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
```

Why these class names?

- The **`section`** wrapper inherits the same vertical rhythm as other sections (36px mobile / 64px desktop). fileciteturn0file3  
- **`.approach-wrap`** constrains width to the **same max width as your split image‑text sections** (`min(1160px, 86vw)`), so the box “reads” as the same component width. fileciteturn0file3  
- **`.box-body split-text` + `ul.list--lg`** lets us reuse your paragraph/list sizing so it matches E/A content exactly. fileciteturn0file3

---

## 2) CSS — add to `assets/css/secondary-maths.css`

Append the following rules (keep them at the end of the file to ensure they win specificity only for this page):

```css
/* ===== Approach box (page‑scoped) ===== */

.section--approach {
  /* Keep section text left‑aligned like the split sections */
  text-align: left;
}

/* Match the split layout container width: min(1160px, 86vw) */
.section--approach .approach-wrap {
  max-width: min(1160px, 86vw);
  margin: 0 auto;
}

/* The card itself: rounded, theme‑aware border and text */
.section--approach .approach-box {
  background: transparent;        /* follows section background */
  color: var(--text);             /* black in light, white in dark */
  border: 1px solid var(--text);  /* black in light, white in dark */
  border-radius: clamp(16px, 2.2vw, 24px);
  padding: clamp(22px, 3.6vw, 40px); /* same comfort range as testimonial cards */
}

/* Large centered title: clone the split-section title sizing */
.section--approach .box-title {
  margin: 0 0 clamp(10px, 1.2vw, 18px);
  text-align: center;
  font-weight: 800;
  line-height: 1.1;
  font-size: clamp(2.1rem, 3.4vw, 3.1rem); /* mirrors .section--split .section-title */
}

/* Constrain line length like your split text block */
.section--approach .box-body {
  max-width: 68ch;   /* same as .section--split .split-text */
  margin: 0 auto;    /* center within the card */
}

/* Paragraph sizing + spacing = same as split sections */
.section--approach .box-body p {
  font-size: clamp(1.06rem, 0.6rem + 1vw, 1.25rem);
  line-height: 1.7;
  margin: 0 0 clamp(10px, 1.4vw, 18px);
}

/* Lists: mirror spacing/indent; li sizes come from your .list--lg rule */
.section--approach .box-body :is(ul, ol) {
  margin: 0 0 clamp(10px, 1.4vw, 18px);
  padding-left: clamp(22px, 2.2vw, 30px);
}
```

**What this matches:**

- **Container width:** identical to `.section--split .split { max-width: min(1160px, 86vw) }` so the box occupies roughly the same width as the image‑text sections. fileciteturn0file3  
- **Title sizing:** uses the same clamp as `.section--split .section-title`, only centered here. fileciteturn0file3  
- **Paragraph sizing:** copied from `.section--split .split-text p`. fileciteturn0file3  
- **List sizing:** your `.split-text ul.list--lg > li` rule already sets the larger list font; by keeping `split-text` and `list--lg`, the box inherits it. fileciteturn0file3  
- **Comfortable padding:** matches the feel of your testimonial/card components (`clamp(22px, 3.6vw, 40px)`), so spacing is consistent. fileciteturn0file3  
- **Theme‑aware colors:** `var(--text)` resolves to **black in light** and **white in dark** (set in your design tokens), so both the **text and border** automatically flip by theme. fileciteturn0file3

---

## 3) Notes & small gotcha (background alternation)

Your main content alternates section backgrounds using `nth-child(odd/even)` under `#main-content`. Inserting this new section as the first child will flip the light/alt backgrounds of the later sections. If you want to **preserve** the current backgrounds of “Elementary Maths” and “Additional Maths” exactly as before, add this optional override:

```css
/* Optional: lock backgrounds so adding the Approach section doesn't flip colors */
#main-content > #e-maths { background: var(--bg); }
#main-content > #additional-maths { background: var(--bg-alt); }
```

(Otherwise, it’s fine to let them swap.) fileciteturn0file3

---

## 4) Why this is responsive by construction

- All sizes use your existing `clamp(...)` scales, so **mobile through desktop** is already covered. fileciteturn0file3  
- Width is capped like the split sections, with centered inner content (`max-width: 68ch`), preventing overly long lines. fileciteturn0file3

---

### Quick test checklist

1. Toggle theme (your toggle sets `data-theme="dark"/"light"`): verify the **border flips** with text color. fileciteturn0file1 fileciteturn0file3  
2. Resize down to ≤900px to confirm it still reads comfortably and matches the **typographic scale** of the E/A sections. fileciteturn0file3  
3. If desired, apply the optional background override in §3.

If you’d like, I can also sketch content guidelines (e.g., suggested subsections/bullets) tuned for quick scanning and SEO, but the structure above satisfies your: **rounded box, centered large title, paragraph + list content, matched fonts/spacings, theme‑aware colors, and responsive width**.

Got it — two surgical tweaks:

- **Enlarge the first and last paragraphs** in the approach box to the same **“lead” scale** used under the *Elementary Maths* and *Additional Maths* section headings, so the hierarchy feels consistent. fileciteturn0file3  
- **Thicken the box border** while keeping it theme‑aware (`var(--text)` → white in dark mode, black in light). fileciteturn0file3

> **Where to edit:** append the snippet below to `assets/css/secondary-maths.css` (this file is already linked from `secondary-school-maths.html`). fileciteturn0file0 fileciteturn0file2 fileciteturn0file1

```css
/* ===== PATCH: Approach box text + border ===== */

/* Make the 1st and last paragraphs bigger (match .section--split .lead) */
.section--approach .box-body p:is(:first-of-type, :last-of-type) {
  /* Mirrors the lead paragraph scale used in E/A sections */
  font-size: clamp(1.18rem, 1.05rem + 1.2vw, 1.6rem); /* ← same as .section--split .lead */
  line-height: 1.7;
  margin: 0 0 clamp(10px, 1.6vw, 20px);              /* ← same spacing as .lead */
}

/* Tablet/phone adjustment: keep parity with .section--split .lead at ≤1200px */
@media (max-width: 1199.98px) {
  .section--approach .box-body p:is(:first-of-type, :last-of-type) {
    font-size: clamp(1.02rem, 0.9rem + 0.8vw, 1.35rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
}

/* Thicker, theme-aware border for the card */
.section--approach .approach-box {
  border-width: 2px; /* was 1px; text color var(--text) already flips by theme */
}
```

### Why this stays consistent
- Those `font-size` and `margin` values **exactly mirror** the `.section--split .lead` rules already used under your “Elementary Maths” and “Additional Maths” titles, so the visual rhythm and hierarchy remain uniform. fileciteturn0file3  
- The `@media (max-width: 1199.98px)` block reproduces the same **tablet/phone scaling** as your existing lead paragraphs. fileciteturn0file3  
- The border still uses `var(--text)`, so it’s **white in dark mode** and **black in light mode**, matching your global tokens. fileciteturn0file3

---

#### Optional (more robust, if you might add more paragraphs later)
If you plan to insert additional paragraphs before/after the list, the `:first-of-type` / `:last-of-type` targeting could become brittle. In that case, add a `class="lead"` to the two paragraphs in your approach HTML and replace the first rule with:

```css
.section--approach .box-body p.lead {
  font-size: clamp(1.18rem, 1.05rem + 1.2vw, 1.6rem);
  line-height: 1.7;
  margin: 0 0 clamp(10px, 1.6vw, 20px);
}
@media (max-width: 1199.98px) {
  .section--approach .box-body p.lead {
    font-size: clamp(1.02rem, 0.9rem + 0.8vw, 1.35rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
}
```

Same look, but **explicitly** marked paragraphs.

---

**Cache busting tip:** if you don’t immediately see the changes, bump the query version on the page’s stylesheet link (e.g., `secondary-maths.css?v=1.0.5`) to invalidate the browser cache. fileciteturn0file1

If you’d prefer the border even bolder, `border-width: 3px;` will still sit well with your design; 2px just matches the weight you already use for other bordered UI (e.g., arrow discs) and keeps the card refined. fileciteturn0file3

