### Optional (cleaner, single source of truth)
If you’d like the **same values** to drive both the list text colour and the Approach border, define a variable once and reuse it:

```css
/* 1) Theme-scoped accent variable */
:root[data-theme="light"] { --list-accent: #660066; }  /* dark magenta */
:root[data-theme="dark"]  { --list-accent: #ffbd44; }  /* bright orange */

/* 2) Use it for ALL non-hero lists (your earlier rule) */
#main-content .section li {
  color: var(--list-accent);
}

/* 3) And for the Approach box border */
.section--approach .approach-box {
  border-color: var(--list-accent);
}
```

This prevents the border and list colours from ever drifting apart.

